text: Kazanka () is a rural locality (a village) in Kazanbulaksky Selsoviet, Zianchurinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 303 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 90 km from Isyangulovo, 5 km from Idelbakovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zianchurinsky District
title: Kazanka, Zianchurinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
